# Python superiority evidence gate

When the task or branch uses `python-superiority` or
`cursor/python-superiority-loop-*`, load and obey
`.cursor/agents/python-superiority.md`.

- Forge unavailable means **Blocked**; never substitute a plan-only PR.
- Projected LOC, parse time, and compile time are not performance evidence.
- One file cycle and at most one open campaign draft PR at a time.
- An optimization PR requires measured baseline/champion latency and memory,
  exact oracle and full-suite results, and the Forge task id.
- A one-file-to-many refactor is one logical bundle. Measure the same end-to-end
  entry point across the exact base and head; never aggregate by summing or
  averaging isolated file percentages.
- Freeze the method before any production edit or official baseline. ORIGINAL
  must be the exact landed code, never a surrogate.
- Team/hive output is diagnostic. Approval compares exact ORIGINAL with the
  final combined candidate after any Swarm refinement.
- Keep raw methods and receipts private until independent Codex reproduction;
  the public PR carries only approved product code, tests, and the minimal
  reproducible table.
- A no-win cycle opens no PR. A refactor-plan PR must state why function-level
  Swarm search is blocked and label all forecasts **projected, not measured**.
